Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} on high heat for the pasta.

Add the @penne pasta{180} and @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

While the pasta cooks, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir the @creme fraiche{150} and @vegetable stock paste{10} into the garlic.

Add the @water{150%ml} and stir to combine.

Simmer, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has reduced and thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Add the @peas{120} to the sauce, then add the @baby spinach{100} a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once the penne is cooked, add to the sauce and stir to coat well.

Stir through the @fresh pesto{50} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40}.

Share your creamy pesto pasta between your #bowls{}.

Enjoy!